Ackermann to Play Key Role in Greek Debt Negotiations, Bild Says

-- B y   R i c h a r d   W e i s s
-- 
2011-10-16T13:55:18Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-16/ackermann-to-play-key-role-in-greek-debt-negotiations-bild-says.html
Deutsche Bank AG Chief Executive
Officer  Josef Ackermann  will play a “central” role in upcoming
negotiations over the possible writing down of Greek bonds by as
much as 50 percent,  Bild  reported.  Ackermann will participate in his capacity as head of the
 Institute of International Finance , the newspaper said, citing
people familiar with the matter.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Richard Weiss in Frankfurt at 
 rweiss5@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Benedikt Kammel at 
 bkammel@bloomberg.net  